	   <tr><td colspan=2>Even with a base str of 103, I too found Bronze to be just too heavy.&nbsp;&nbsp;So at level 16 I finally started working on acquiring something else.<br><br>Jagged Bands are certainly worth the cost.  I managed to get 2 for only 50pp.  At AC5 and +3 str (each) I was eager to lay out the money.<br><br>Golden Amber Earrings do not provide any AC, but at +3 Str and only costing around 30-40pp for 2, well, easy decision.<br><br>Fine Plate Greaves were an excellent addition in many ways.  They dropped weight from the bronze while providing a point or two more AC.  To say they look better is an understatement as well.  The only drawback is the cost.  Where bronze greaves prices are now down around 10-15pp, fine plate greaves must be made and materials alone will probably take you to 200pp.<br><br>Fine Plate Boots proved to be a similar situation to the greaves.  Expect costs of over 125pp.<br><br>A Skull-shaped barbute will often go for 200pp and provides AC13 with a nice little HP boost.  If you can swing a BI crown the AC is not as good (AC 5), but the crown provides some very nice benefits that are not always obvious.  +5 str and +5 on all save categories in one item can be a godsend.  On a human it also looks much much better than the buckethead/bullethead fashions offered by bronze helms.<br><br>A straw-spun belt is AC10, but weighs in at a costly 6 stone.  However, prices seem to be dropping.  I managed to buy mine for only 30pp.<br><br>A spiked collar has proven to be the most beneficial for the cost.  These have gotten so common that 4pp seems to be the average price.  At +3 str in the neck slot with a little AC as well, the low cost astounded me.<br><br>The above are items that I bought with some hard-earned money.  From good friends and very nice people that took pity on a paladin, I managed to garner the following (which I have yet to find better):  Charred Guardian BP, Darkmail Gaunts, Silver Bracers, and Grotesque Mask.<br><br>Lanceor<br>Paladin of Mithanial Marr<br>Acceptor of 23 truths<br>Xegony Server<br><br>Perception is reality, but truth is virtuous.<br>-Mithian proverb<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
