<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=97335950315417></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97335950315417><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=97335950315417>RE: Obtaining cash during your teen levels</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=97335950315417#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Nov 4th 12:38 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree with many of Lanceor's points regarding acquiring loot in the teen levels, and have some points of my own.<br><br>First, spend as much time hunting and as little time travelling from place to place as possible. Even if you kill mobs that give you no exp you'll eventually get a number of items (cloth armor or a cracked staff off an orc pawn here, a medium quality pelt there) that vendors will take off your hands for a modest sum. Kill early and often, and the vendors will reward you over time; you'll be amazed how quickly the gold and silver add up.<br><br>Second, from personal experience I made a good deal of plat from something as common as bone chips. Kill every skel and decaying skel you can find, and before long you'll have several stacks of bone chips. Then, wait for the well-off, desperate necro hoping to buy chips, and they'll often pay a premium if you can help them out. On one occasion, I received 18 plat for 3 stacks; on another occasion, I received 40 plat for 2 stacks! In any event, expect at least 3 to 4 plat per stack.<br><br>Lastly, learn to recognize a bargain. This requires some savvy, but often someone will offer to sell an item for a very attractive price just to get rid of it. Take a chance and buy the item, in hopes of selling it for a tidy profit. This is somewhat risky if you're not familiar with price trends, but it can be very profitable. On one occasion, I bought some dark mail gauntlets from someone for 100 plat, and sold them an hour later for 250 plat.<br><br>As for hunting grounds for teen levels, I prefer ec and wc, (ec in particular if you're looking to buy and sell items at auction) and oasis for orcs and mummies, which frequently drop bronze and gems, respectively. Hope this helped.<br><br>Canthiel<br>A 24th lvl pally<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
