	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've found that, despite the greater damage that a 2-hander does, the more frequent hits of a 1-hander seem to agro the critter almost as well. When a critter agros on your caster and you have a slow 2-hander, you could be waiting precious time to get the critter off them. I've also found that Bashing is similar to Stun, it agros the critters on you almost instantly. Maybe what I see is only my biases, but we each have our own preferences. The important thing is to develop a style of play that you prefer. And remember that different situations call for different tactics. Keep both 1h and 2h maxed out once you pass the 20s.<br>&nbsp;<br>________<br><br>I've travelled this world and have seen many wondrous things. You are not one of them.</td></tr>
