	   <tr><td colspan=2>I, like most melee types, started using 1hs from the get-go, but I remember thinking to myself, after my 1hs was up around 40 (lvl 6 or 7 I guess) that 2hs seemed pretty cool, and looked much cooler when used.. so I found myself a rusty 2hs and went to work.. I think was really kept me going with it was a couple of rather fortuitous donations by higher level characters..the most noteworthy being an Axe of the Iron Back (16 dmg, 37dly) given to me when I was level 10 or so.&nbsp;&nbsp;Since then I've been working on 2hs incessently..I love faster weapons as opposed to high damage, so the AiB was perfect.. and I eventually got into a Gigantic Zweihander, and currently use a Runic Carver.. (18/37, great weapon).  What I have found is that there are a lot more readily available, Paladin friendly 2hs weapons at mid-level (I'm currently 31) than there are 1hs.. plus with double attack being as handy as it is.. 2hs is just so nicely effective.  Unfortunately NOW I wish that I had gotten my 1hs up when I was lower level.. there are certain situations (fighting casters, for instance) when 1hs plus shield would be very handy, and with nice Paladin 1 handers like the GB and Deep Six Cutlass around.. it's a good skill to learn.  In the long run, I think I'll be a 2hs man forever..but its nice to be adaptable.  Be the best Paladin that you can be.. learn it all.<br><br>Prad Darkbane<br>Level 31 Paladin<br>Vallon Zek Server<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
