	   <tr><td colspan=2>I will concur with the others who have answered your post.<br><br>Strength takes priority.<br><br>The spells a paladin gets are fair, but hardly going to be the means by which you take down your opponent.&nbsp;&nbsp;Wisdom is nice to have since it provides more mana for spells, but it is not the primary ability.<br><br>I once met a female erudite paladin.  She failed to put any points into strength when she began.  Her strength was only 70 and by level 15 she was having all sorts of difficulties wearing bronze armor and carrying a single weapon.  <br><br>If all this does not convince you then how about this: prior to level 20 there is a damage cap for all characters.  At level 20, when it is finally lifted, you will see a 2-handed sword do about an extra 10 points of damage on every hit.  Strength adds to damage...  on every hit.<br><br>Lanceor<br>Paladin of Mithaniel Marr<br>Acceptor of 23 truths<br>Xegony Server<br><br>Perception is reality, but truth is virtuous.<br>-Mithian proverb<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
