	   <tr><td colspan=2>I tended to hunt in Unrest quite a bit from my late teens to early 20's. It's quite dangerous there, but the experience is great and you get to play with your new ward all day long, which if you're lvl 15 or a bit higher, you'll be wanting to practice with as much as possible to get your evoke up. <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;It's a given fact that if you hunt in Unrest you're going to die at least once a day (if you're an uber-character and never die anywhere, don't flame me, most people do die in Unrest all the time) But in the low teens you should be making much more xp then you'll lose with a death.<br>  The best part about hunting in Unrest at an early level is that later on when you go there with your guild or to camp something with others you'll be the guy in the know who tells them what to avoid and where to hide, and they'll appreciate that in this zone<br><br>Grimjrakar ver'Magnussen<br>Paladin of the Fourth Wall<br>Tarew Marr<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
