<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9703841624474></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9703841624474><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=9703841624474>RE: help a lvl 10 Paladin</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=9703841624474#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Oct 1st 3:09 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well...having played my paladin to lvl 18...I'll offer what advice that I have gathered.<br><br>My paladin is a High Elf, therefore, I've got the problem of Str coming up many a time. First get Str buffing items. The collors that the gnoll commies drop in the bottom of BlackBurrow give a decent little addition. Also, try going to GFay and buying Jagged Bands...get 2!!! they are +5str and and 2AC and go on the fingers. Also, decide if you want to use 1HS or 2HS and ditch the other. I prefer 1hs (faster dly and bash) over the the dmg dealt by 2HS *yes I know FA is 2HS*<br><br>The next armor up is Bronze, but if you're carrying so much that you get encumbered with banded...stay with banded. I would stay with combine for a little while. I'm not too sure what comes after it...my pally has had his Combine for 6seasons and is a bit attached to it. <br><br>Depending on where you are determines where you should hunt.<br><br>Qeynos Area - BlackBurrow and WK<br>FP - E/Wcommons, Nro<br>GFay - Crushbone and some areas of Butcherblock.<br><br>Good luck with you friend.<br><br>Freman<br>Lvl 18 Pally...currently dining at KFC in SK.<br>Bertoxx<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
